Sentiment analysis refers to the process of determining the emotional tone or attitude conveyed by a piece of writing, in this case, social media posts; 
Engagement rate is a metric that measures the level of interaction by followers with an influencer's or campaign's content; 
Influencer impact here is determined by the influencer's follower count and engagement rate, indicating the potential reach and effectiveness of a campaign; 
Content usage metrics provide insights into the types of media used in a campaign (e.g., images, videos, text posts).
